[8] Australia (ACT)
Date: Fri 18 Jul 2014
Source: The Canberra Times [abridged, edited]
http://www.canberratimes.com.au/act-news/measles-case-diagnosed-in-canberra-on-friday-20140718-zuoj5.html


A spokesman for ACT [Australian Capital Territory] Health confirmed a single case [of measles] on Friday [18 Jul 2014] evening and said more information should be available on Saturday.

The ACT acting chief health officer said members of the public could have been exposed to measles virus at Kaleen Plaza Shopping Centre and Kaleen Supabarn between 10 am and noon on Wednesday [16 Jul 2014]. "We're advising anyone who attended this shopping centre at these times to be aware for symptoms and to seek medical advice if they develop," Dr Pengilley said. Dr Pengilley said anyone with symptoms of measles should advise their health provider before they arrive at a medical clinic so infection control measures could be undertaken.

The recent confirmed case was the 3rd for the ACT this year [2014], after one in January 2014 and another in early February 2014. Before that, Canberra had not had a confirmed infection since 2011.

