[9] Australia (Tasmania)
Date: Thu 17 Jul 2014
Source: 7 TV News [abridged, edited]
https://au.news.yahoo.com/a/24486739/tasmania-confirms-1st-cases-of-measles-in-5-years/


Health authorities have confirmed the 1st cases of measles in Tasmania in 5 years. A man in the state's south and a teenager in the northwest have both been isolated to minimise the chance of the virus spreading. "There are several other cases on which we're awaiting test results," said Director of Public Health Dr Roscoe Taylor. The Health Department has contacted more than 100 people it says are at risk of infection, and it believes several more cases are likely. The 2 confirmed cases are separate, and both people have recently travelled interstate or internationally.

After years without a case of measles in the state, Dr Taylor said it was unusual to have 2 separate cases occur at the same time. "Why, at this particular time of year? Where suddenly [there are] some cases, it makes me wonder whether or not there are some full-blown instances of transmission occurring elsewhere in the world," he said.

